I'd like to report a typo in the Spring AI documentation section on Chat Client API "Default System Text with parameters."(https://docs.spring.io/spring-ai/reference/api/chatclient.html) Specifically, in the example for the Default System Text with parameters.

The current example contains extra parentheses after 'content' :

```
@RestController
class AIController {
	private final ChatClient chatClient
	AIController(ChatClient chatClient) {
		this.chatClient = chatClient;
	}
	@GetMapping("/ai")
	Map<String, String> completion(@RequestParam(value = "message", defaultValue = "Tell me a joke") String message, String voice) {
		return Map.of(
				"completion",
				chatClient.prompt()
						.system(sp -> sp.param("voice", voice))
						.user(message)
						.call()
						.content());
	}
}
```
However, based on my understanding, it should likely be :
(After removing extra parentheses)
```
@RestController
class AIController {
	private final ChatClient chatClient
	AIController(ChatClient chatClient) {
		this.chatClient = chatClient;
	}
	@GetMapping("/ai")
	Map<String, String> completion(@RequestParam(value = "message", defaultValue = "Tell me a joke") String message, String voice) {
		return Map.of(
				"completion",
				chatClient.prompt()
						.system(sp -> sp.param("voice", voice))
						.user(message)
						.call()
						.content();
	}
}
```

I'd like to report a typo in the Spring AI documentation section on Chat Client API "Returning an Entity."(https://docs.spring.io/spring-ai/reference/api/chatclient.html) Specifically, in the example for the parameterizedTypeReference.

The current example shows:
```
List<ActorFilms> actorFilms = chatClient.prompt()
    .user("Generate the filmography of 5 movies for Tom Hanks and Bill Murray.")
    .call()
    .entity(new ParameterizedTypeReference<List<ActorsFilms>>() {
    });
```
However, based on my understanding, it should likely be:
```
List<ActorFilms> actorFilms = chatClient.prompt()
    .user("Generate the filmography of 5 movies for Tom Hanks and Bill Murray.")
    .call()
    .entity(new ParameterizedTypeReference<List<ActorFilms>>() {
    });
```
This change would ensure the reference captures a list of ActorFilms objects.
